description: This 3-level townhome charmer tucked in Candlestick Cove boasts 1,878-SF interior lined in hardwoods and appointed w/ ample windows. Guests are met w/ an open concept that seamlessly merges living/dining/kitchen in one bright, airy expanse. Decked in granite, an eat-in kitchen is poised for dinner parties, with S/S appliances and peninsula island with bar seating. Perfect for a growing family, 2 bedrooms, a full bath, and laundry lie on the main floor. The 3rd floor is a sumptuous retreat, equipped w/ a sprawling primary suite w/ his/hers walk-in closets, luxe ensuite bath and cozy den. The ground floor includes a guest suite, full bath, and 2-car garage w/ side-by-side parking. Located near Highway 280/101 and Cal Train, 121 Otter Cove offers free shuttle service to Glen Park BART. A pet-friendly community w/ shared gardens and play areas, the association fee includes common area maintenance, exterior maintenance, professional mgmt, water. The property is virtually staged.

Tranquility and stunning Western & Eastern-facing Ocean and Bay Views are showcased in this modern 3 bedroom, 1.5 bath townhome atop Everson ridge between Glen Park and Noe Valley. The light-filled main level boasts views of Downtown, Mt. Diablo, the Bay and beyond from the living room and private balcony, and of the Southern Hills from the dining room. The open kitchen features maple cabinets, stainless steel appliances, honed black granite counters with custom tile accents, and an eating bar. Enjoy unique architectural details, a fireplace, Brazilian hardwood floors and recessed lighting throughout the level, along with a large half bath. On the top level, the rear bedroom has a walk-in closet and city views. The spacious and sunny primary bedroom has views of the Southern Hills and Pacific, plus ample custom closet space. A full bath sits between. The third bedroom or home office is on the entry level with direct access to a private and peaceful patio/garden.

The residence at 2405 Folsom St No. 5 is a spacious and modern home in a vibrant neighborhood. The three-level home was built in 2008 and has been nicely updated since then. The floor plan is generous and includes two terraces that provide plenty of natural light and space, making it feel like a single-family home. On the first floor, there is a living, dining area and kitchen that runs from the front to the back of the residence. This area also includes an attached terrace. The second level is just as bright and spacious and features two ensuite bedrooms and a laundry room. Finally, the third level is dedicated entirely to the primary suite, which includes a large spa-like bathroom, walk-in closet, wet bar, and a large outdoor terrace. In addition to the ample living space, the residence also comes with two car parking. Overall, this is a comfortable and convenient living space in one of the best locations in the city.

The best parts of San Francisco are at your fingertips in this centrally located Hayes Valley Townhouse. This condo gem has the feeling of a single family home with no one above or below you. The lower level of this home consists of two quiet bedrooms as well as a full remodeled bathroom with new tile shower and quartz vanity. The highlight of this property is in the upstairs, sun-drenched great room. This room, with vaulted ceilings, is large enough for a spacious living room setup and a dining nook as well. With the attached kitchen, this layout is perfect for entertaining guest. The fully remodeled chef's kitchen boasts all new cabinets, all new hardware, new quartz countertops, new tile backsplash and all new stainless steel appliances. This upstairs room enjoys all day sun with massive south facing windows and multiple skylights. The home has also enjoyed all new interior paint, new engineered wood floors, new lighting throughout and updated electrical. Enjoy some green space in the Hayes Valley sun with shared yard in the back of the property. The world is at your fingertips with the best parts of San Francisco and Hayes Valley within walking distance of this home.

Make this stunning, remodeled residence your own San Francisco retreat.  A private 2-level two bedroom, 2.5-bath townhouse with a garden patio facing the courtyard. The first floor consists of the living room with wall-to-wall windows, a cozy wood-burning fireplace, and a gracious dining room opening to the large patio-perfect for dining al fresco & the urban gardener.  A powder room with a laundry closet completes this level.   Upstairs is the large primary suite with double closets, a bathroom with shower & tub,  a second bedroom, a hall bath, and oversized storage closets. There is a second entrance on this floor. There is one car garage parking & additional storage.  Telegraph Landing has a lovely staff, including a 24-hour security doorman/guard, an excellent on-site manager, and an assistant. Amenities include a gym, club room, and two common area roof decks with Bay and Golden Gate Bridge views & communal gardens.  Enjoy this outstanding location. Walk to The Embarcadero, Ferry Building, Bay Club, the Battery, the acclaimed Farmers Market, Exploratorium, Levi Plaza, Bay Club & many outstanding neighborhood restaurants. One of San Francisco''s most sought-after neighborhoods.

Welcome to 101 W. Crystal Cove Terrace in San Francisco.  Enjoy waterfront living in an exclusive townhome complex in a serene and peaceful neighborhood at Candlestick Cove.    This corner tri-level townhome feels almost like a single-family home, with its own entrance via a front yard that is maintained by the HOA. The home features 3 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms, a patio, and a 2-car garage with side-by-side parking. The first floor has one bedroom and one bathroom, perfect for guests or extended family. On the second floor is the main living area, with the living/dining room, kitchen, patio, and half bathroom. This layout is ideal for both privacy and family time. Finally, on the top floor are two master bedrooms with en-suite bathrooms. All three bedrooms are carpeted, and there is tile flooring in the living areas. The kitchen has stainless steel appliances, and an in-unit washer and dryer complete the home. Its HOA dues are very reasonable, at $451 per month. Candlestick Cove is a great community with barbecue areas, a playground, lush green gardens, and walking trails along the nearby waterfront.
